cd ClientApp
npm install
cd ..

To use Entity Framework Core with a SQL Server database, run the following dotnet CLI command:
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.SqlServer

To add support for an InMemory data source, for testing:
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.InMemory

install entity framework
dotnet add package Npgsql.EntityFrameworkCore.PostgreSQL --version 5.0.2

install dotnet-ef tool, to use dotnet migrations
dotnet tool install --global dotnet-ef

install the entityframework design
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Design --version 5.0.5

Time to add our initial migration. Run this command to the terminal.
The migrations feature in EF Core provides a way to incrementally update the database schema to keep it in sync with the application's data model while preserving existing data in the database.
Sometimes is necesarly to restart the IDE	
dotnet ef migrations add InitialMigration
